 ### Model Check

The structure of the model is correct.  
However, **there is a unit inconsistency in the vitamin constraint**:

- The table gives vitamin content **per kg in mg**.
- The requirement is **100 mg**, while protein and minerals are in grams.
- To maintain consistent units and better numerical scaling, it is preferable to convert vitamins from **mg to g**.

Since  
\[
100\text{ mg} = 0.1\text{ g}
\]
and  
\[
1\text{ mg} = 0.001\text{ g},
\]
we convert vitamin coefficients to grams.

