The structure of the original model was essentially correct. After verifying timing consistency and clarifying year transitions, the above formulation is the final clean and fully correct linear programming model.
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Create model
model = gp.Model("Hongyin_Fund_Optimization")

# Decision variables (all >= 0 by default)
F = model.addVar(lb=0, name="F")

A = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=60, name="A")   # Bond A
B = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=90, name="B")   # Bond B
C = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=50, name="C")   # Bond C

D03 = model.addVar(lb=0, name="D03")
D04 = model.addVar(lb=0, name="D04")
D05 = model.addVar(lb=0, name="D05")
D06 = model.addVar(lb=0, name="D06")

# Objective: Minimize total funds raised
model.setObjective(F, GRB.MINIMIZE)

# Constraints

# Beginning of 2003
model.addConstr(F == 100 + A + B + D03, name="CashFlow_2003")

# Beginning of 2004
model.addConstr(1.04 * D03 == 150 + C + D04, name="CashFlow_2004")

# Beginning of 2005
model.addConstr(1.04 * D04 + 1.25 * B == 120 + D05, name="CashFlow_2005")

# Beginning of 2006
