This is the required linear programming model for minimizing the total annual cost under the delivery contract requirements.
【验证之后的模型】:
 The model is essentially correct.  
Only one refinement improves precision:

- Since deliveries must exactly meet contract quantities and there is no reason to hold ending inventory after Q4, it is better to **fix \(I_4 = 0\)** (not charge holding cost for \(I_4\), or equivalently keep it but it will be zero).
- The structure can be slightly simplified while remaining fully linear and suitable for Gurobi.

Below is the **optimized and final linear programming model**.

---

# ✅ Final Mathematical Model

## Decision Variables

\[
x_t = \text{production in quarter } t \quad (t=1,2,3,4)
\]

\[
I_t = \text{inventory at end of quarter } t \quad (t=1,2,3,4)
\]

---

## Objective Function

Minimize total annual cost (thousand yuan):

\[
\min Z =
12x_1 + 11x_2 + 11.5x_3 + 12.5x_4
+ 0.1(I_1 + I_2 + I_3)
\]

(Note: \(I_4=0\), so no holding cost is incurred after Q4.)

---

## Constraints

### 1️⃣ Inventory Balance Constraints

\[
I_1 = x_1 - 15
\]

\[
I_2 = I_1 + x_2 - 20
\]

\[
I_3 = I_2 + x_3 - 25
\]

\[
I_4 = I_3 + x_4 - 20
\]

---

### 2️⃣ Contract Satisfaction (No Ending Inventory)

\[
I_4 = 0
\]

---

### 3️⃣ Production Capacity Constraints

\[
x_1 \le 25
\]

\[
x_2 \le 35
\]

\[
x_3 \le 30
\]

\[
x_4 \le 20
\]

---

### 4️⃣ Nonnegativity Constraints

\[
x_t \ge 0, \quad I_t \ge 0
\qquad (t=1,2,3,4)
\]

---

✅ This is the correct and optimized linear programming formulation, fully consistent with the problem statement and directly suitable for Gurobi implementation.
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Data
quarters = range(1, 5)
capacity = {1: 25, 2: 35, 3: 30, 4: 20}
demand = {1: 15, 2: 20, 3: 25, 4: 20}
prod_cost = {1: 12.0, 2: 11.0, 3: 11.5, 4: 12.5}
holding_cost = 0.1

# Create model
model = gp.Model("Production_Planning")

# Decision variables
x = model.addVars(quarters, lb=0, name="Production")
I = model.addVars(quarters, lb=0, name="Inventory")

# Objective function
model.setObjective(
    gp.quicksum(prod_cost[t] * x[t] for t in quarters) +
    holding_cost * gp.quicksum(I[t] for t in [1, 2, 3]),
    GRB.MINIMIZE
)

# Inventory balance constraints
model.addConstr(I[1] == x[1] - demand[1], name="Inventory_Balance_1")
model.addConstr(I[2] == I[1] + x[2] - demand[2], name="Inventory_Balance_2")
model.addConstr(I[3] == I[2] + x[3] - demand[3], name="Inventory_Balance_3")
model.addConstr(I[4] == I[3] + x[4] - demand[4], name="Inventory_Balance_4")

# Ending inventory must be zero
model.addConstr(I[4] == 0, name="Ending_Inventory_Zero")

# Production capacity constraints
for t in quarters:
    model.addConstr(x[t] <= capacity[t], name=f"Capacity_{t}")

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal Total Cost: {model.objVal:.2f} thousand yuan")
    for t in quarters:
        print(f"Quarter {t}: Production = {x[t].x:.2f}, Inventory = {I[t].x:.2f}")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
