### 3. Decision Variables

\[
x_{it} \ge 0 \quad \text{production quantity of product } i \text{ in stage } t
\]

\[
I_{it} \ge 0 \quad \text{inventory of product } i \text{ at end of stage } t
\]

\[
s_{it} \ge 0 \quad \text{shortage (stockout) of product } i \text{ in stage } t
\]

\[
h_t^+ \ge 0 \quad \text{equipment overload at stage } t
\]

\[
k_t^+ \ge 0 \quad \text{capital excess at stage } t
\]

---

### 4. Inventory Balance Constraints

\[
I_{i,t-1} + x_{it} + s_{it} = D_{it} + I_{it}
\qquad \forall i,t
\]

\[
I_{i0}=0,\qquad I_{i3}=0
\]

---

### 5. Equipment Capacity Goal Constraint

\[
\sum_{i=1}^3 a_i x_{it} - h_t^+ \le H
\qquad \forall t
\]

---

### 6. Working Capital Goal Constraint

\[
\sum_{i=1}^3 c_i x_{it} - k_t^+ \le K
\qquad \forall t
\]

---

### 7. Multi‑Priority Goal Programming Model

#### Priority 1 (highest): Minimize weighted shortages

\[
\min Z_1 = \sum_{t=1}^3 \sum_{i=1}^3 w_i s_{it}
\]

#### Priority 2: Minimize equipment overload

\[
\min Z_2 = \sum_{t=1}^3 h_t^+
\]

#### Priority 3: Minimize capital excess

\[
\min Z_3 = \sum_{t=1}^3 k_t^+
\]

---

### 8. Preemptive Goal Programming Form

Lexicographic optimization:

\[
\text{Lex min } (Z_1,\; Z_2,\; Z_3)
\]

---

### Complete Mathematical Model

\[
\textbf{Lex min } 
\left(
\sum_{t}\sum_{i} w_i s_{it},\;
\sum_t h_t^+,\;
\sum_t k_t^+
\right)
\]

Subject to:

\[
I_{i,t-1} + x_{it} + s_{it} = D_{it} + I_{it}
\qquad \forall i,t
\]

\[
\sum_i a_i x_{it} - h_t^+ \le H
\qquad \forall t
\]

\[
\sum_i c_i x_{it} - k_t^+ \le K
\qquad \forall t
\]

\[
I_{i0}=0,\quad I_{i3}=0
\]

\[
x_{it}, I_{it}, s_{it}, h_t^+, k_t^+ \ge 0
\]

