    Factories $A_1$ and $A_2$ produce a certain type of material. Due to high demand and insufficient supply, a new factory needs to be built. There are two construction options: $A_3$ and $A_4$. The material is needed in four locations: $B_1, B_2, B_3, B_4$. The annual production capacities of each factory, the annual demand at each location, and the unit transportation cost of materials from each factory to each demand location $c_{ij}$ (in thousand yuan per kiloton, where i,j = 1,2,3,4) are shown in Table 5-2. 

\begin{table}[h]
    \centering
    \caption{Table 5-2: Unit Transportation Costs from Factories to Demand Locations}
    \renewcommand{\arraystretch}{1.2}
    \begin{tabular}{c|cccc|c}
        \toprule
        $c_{ij}$ (thousand yuan/kt) & $B_1$ & $B_2$ & $B_3$ & $B_4$ & Production Capacity (kt/year) \\
        \midrule
        $A_1$ & 2 & 9 & 3 & 4 & 400 \\
        $A_2$ & 8 & 3 & 5 & 7 & 600 \\
        $A_3$ & 7 & 6 & 1 & 2 & 200 \\
        $A_4$ & 4 & 5 & 2 & 5 & 200 \\
        \midrule
        Demand (kt/year) & 350 & 400 & 300 & 150 & \\
        \bottomrule
    \end{tabular}
\end{table}

If factory $A_3$ is built, its annual production cost is estimated to be 1200 thousand yuan;if $A_4$ is built, the annual production cost is 1500 thousand yuan.The goal is to decide whether to build factory $A_3$ or $A_4$ in order to minimize the total annual cost, which includes all transportation costs and the production cost(in thousand yuan) of the new factory.

-------------
【数学模型】:
 **Decision Variables**

- \(x_{ij} \ge 0\): quantity transported from factory \(A_i\) to demand location \(B_j\) (kt/year), \(i=1,2,3,4;\; j=1,2,3,4\)

- \(y_3, y_4 \in \{0,1\}\):  
  \[
  y_k =
  \begin{cases}
  1, & \text{if factory } A_k \text{ is built} \\
  0, & \text{otherwise}
  \end{cases}
  \quad k=3,4
  \]

---

### **Objective Function**

Minimize total annual cost (transportation + fixed production cost):

\[
\begin{aligned}
\min Z = 
&\; 2x_{11}+9x_{12}+3x_{13}+4x_{14} \\
&+8x_{21}+3x_{22}+5x_{23}+7x_{24} \\
&+7x_{31}+6x_{32}+1x_{33}+2x_{34} \\
&+4x_{41}+5x_{42}+2x_{43}+5x_{44} \\
&+1200y_3 +1500y_4
\end{aligned}
\]

(All costs in thousand yuan.)

---

### **Constraints**

#### 1. Demand Satisfaction Constraints

\[
\begin{aligned}
x_{11}+x_{21}+x_{31}+x_{41} &= 350 \\
x_{12}+x_{22}+x_{32}+x_{42} &= 400 \\
x_{13}+x_{23}+x_{33}+x_{43} &= 300 \\
x_{14}+x_{24}+x_{34}+x_{44} &= 150
\end{aligned}
\]

---

#### 2. Production Capacity Constraints

Existing factories:

\[
\begin{aligned}
x_{11}+x_{12}+x_{13}+x_{14} &\le 400 \\
x_{21}+x_{22}+x_{23}+x_{24} &\le 600
\end{aligned}
\]

New factory (capacity depends on construction decision):

\[
\begin{aligned}
x_{31}+x_{32}+x_{33}+x_{34} &\le 200\, y_3 \\
x_{41}+x_{42}+x_{43}+x_{44} &\le 200\, y_4
\end{aligned}
\]

---

#### 3. Construction Decision Constraint

Exactly one new factory is built:

\[
y_3 + y_4 = 1
\]

---

#### 4. Variable Domains

\[
x_{ij} \ge 0, \quad y_3,y_4 \in \{0,1\}
\]

