# ✅ Final Mathematical Model (MILP)

## Decision Variables

- \(x_{ij} \ge 0\): amount transported from factory \(A_i\) to demand point \(B_j\) (kt/year),  
  \(i=1,2,3,4;\; j=1,2,3,4\)

- \(y_3, y_4 \in \{0,1\}\):

\[
y_k =
\begin{cases}
1, & \text{if factory } A_k \text{ is built} \\
0, & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\quad k=3,4
\]

---

## Objective Function

Minimize total annual cost (thousand yuan):

\[
\begin{aligned}
\min Z =
&\sum_{j=1}^{4} c_{1j}x_{1j}
+\sum_{j=1}^{4} c_{2j}x_{2j}
+\sum_{j=1}^{4} c_{3j}x_{3j}
+\sum_{j=1}^{4} c_{4j}x_{4j} \\
&+1200y_3 +1500y_4
\end{aligned}
\]

Expanded form:

\[
\begin{aligned}
\min Z =
&2x_{11}+9x_{12}+3x_{13}+4x_{14} \\
&+8x_{21}+3x_{22}+5x_{23}+7x_{24} \\
&+7x_{31}+6x_{32}+1x_{33}+2x_{34} \\
&+4x_{41}+5x_{42}+2x_{43}+5x_{44} \\
&+1200y_3 +1500y_4
\end{aligned}
\]

---

## Constraints

### 1️⃣ Demand Satisfaction

\[
\begin{aligned}
x_{11}+x_{21}+x_{31}+x_{41} &= 350 \\
x_{12}+x_{22}+x_{32}+x_{42} &= 400 \\
x_{13}+x_{23}+x_{33}+x_{43} &= 300 \\
x_{14}+x_{24}+x_{34}+x_{44} &= 150
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 2️⃣ Production Capacity

Existing factories:

\[
\begin{aligned}
x_{11}+x_{12}+x_{13}+x_{14} &\le 400 \\
x_{21}+x_{22}+x_{23}+x_{24} &\le 600
\end{aligned}
\]

New factories (capacity activated only if built):

\[
\begin{aligned}
x_{31}+x_{32}+x_{33}+x_{34} &\le 200\, y_3 \\
x_{41}+x_{42}+x_{43}+x_{44} &\le 200\, y_4
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 3️⃣ Construction Decision

Exactly one new factory is built:

\[
y_3 + y_4 = 1
\]

---

### 4️⃣ Variable Domains

\[
x_{ij} \ge 0
\]

\[
y_3, y_4 \in \{0,1\}
\]

---

# ✅ Model Characteristics

- Mixed-Integer Linear Program (MILP)
- Fixed-charge facility selection + transportation structure
- Correctly enforces exactly one new factory
- Tight big‑M formulation (capacity 200 is the natural tight bound)

---

If desired, the model can be further reduced to a single binary variable formulation for computational compactness, but the current form is already clean and solver‑efficient.
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Create model
model = gp.Model("Factory_Selection_Transportation")

# Sets
factories = [1, 2, 3, 4]
demand_points = [1, 2, 3, 4]

# Transportation costs (thousand yuan per kt)
c = {
    (1,1):2, (1,2):9, (1,3):3, (1,4):4,
    (2,1):8, (2,2):3, (2,3):5, (2,4):7,
    (3,1):7, (3,2):6, (3,3):1, (3,4):2,
    (4,1):4, (4,2):5, (4,3):2, (4,4):5
}

# Production capacities (kt/year)
capacity = {1:400, 2:600, 3:200, 4:200}

# Demand (kt/year)
demand = {1:350, 2:400, 3:300, 4:150}

# Fixed costs (thousand yuan)
fixed_cost = {3:1200, 4:1500}

# Decision variables
x = model.addVars(factories, demand_points, lb=0, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="x")
y = model.addVars([3, 4], vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="y")

# Objective function
transport_cost = gp.quicksum(c[i, j] * x[i, j] for i in factories for j in demand_points)
fixed_cost_term = gp.quicksum(fixed_cost[k] * y[k] for k in [3, 4])
model.setObjective(transport_cost + fixed_cost_term, GRB.MINIMIZE)

# Demand satisfaction constraints
for j in demand_points:
    model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(x[i, j] for i in factories) == demand[j], name=f"demand_{j}")

# Capacity constraints for existing factories
model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(x[1, j] for j in demand_points) <= capacity[1], name="cap_1")
model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(x[2, j] for j in demand_points) <= capacity[2], name="cap_2")

# Capacity constraints for new factories
model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(x[3, j] for j in demand_points) <= capacity[3] * y[3], name="cap_3")
model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(x[4, j] for j in demand_points) <= capacity[4] * y[4], name="cap_4")

# Exactly one new factory is built
model.addConstr(y[3] + y[4] == 1, name="build_one")

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal total cost (thousand yuan): {model.objVal:.2f}")
    print("\nFactory construction decision:")
    for k in [3, 4]:
        print(f"Build A{k}: {int(y[k].x)}")
    print("\nTransportation plan (kt/year):")
    for i in factories:
        for j in demand_points:
            if x[i, j].x > 1e-6:
                print(f"x[{i},{j}] = {x[i,j].x:.2f}")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
```
