【验证之后的模型】:
 The model structure is essentially correct (standard 2‑machine flow shop MILP with position variables).  
However, some constraints can be **tightened and simplified**:

1. The first completion constraint on machine B should be written consistently with the general case.
2. The makespan constraint can be strengthened to apply to all positions (not only the last one).
3. Since the objective minimizes \(C_{\max}\), the recursive completion constraints can safely be written as equalities (tight form), improving numerical behavior.
4. Introduce auxiliary expressions for processing time at position \(k\) to simplify notation.

Below is the **corrected and slightly strengthened final MILP model**.

---

# ✅ Final Mathematical Model (Optimized Form)

---

## Sets

\[
J=\{1,\dots,12\} \quad \text{(jobs)}
\]
\[
K=\{1,\dots,12\} \quad \text{(sequence positions)}
\]

---

## Parameters

\[
p_{jA} = \text{processing time of job } j \text{ on machine A}
\]
\[
p_{jB} = \text{processing time of job } j \text{ on machine B}
\]

---

## Decision Variables

\[
x_{jk} =
\begin{cases}
1 & \text{if job } j \text{ is assigned to position } k \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]

\[
C_{Ak} \ge 0 \quad \text{completion time at position } k \text{ on machine A}
\]

\[
C_{Bk} \ge 0 \quad \text{completion time at position } k \text{ on machine B}
\]

\[
C_{\max} \ge 0 \quad \text{makespan}
\]

---

## Objective

\[
\min C_{\max}
\]

---

## Assignment Constraints

Each position has exactly one job:

\[
\sum_{j\in J} x_{jk} = 1
\qquad \forall k\in K
\]

Each job appears exactly once:

\[
\sum_{k\in K} x_{jk} = 1
\qquad \forall j\in J
\]

---

## Processing Time at Position \(k\)

For compactness define:

\[
P_{Ak} = \sum_{j\in J} p_{jA} x_{jk}
\]
\[
P_{Bk} = \sum_{j\in J} p_{jB} x_{jk}
\]

---

## Machine A Completion Times

First position:

\[
C_{A1} = P_{A1}
\]

Recursion:

\[
C_{Ak} = C_{A,k-1} + P_{Ak}
\qquad \forall k=2,\dots,12
\]

---

## Machine B Completion Times

First position:

\[
C_{B1} \ge C_{A1} + P_{B1}
\]

Recursion (flow shop precedence + machine availability):

\[
C_{Bk} \ge C_{Ak} + P_{Bk}
\qquad \forall k\in K
\]

\[
C_{Bk} \ge C_{B,k-1} + P_{Bk}
\qquad \forall k=2,\dots,12
\]

---

## Makespan Definition (Strengthened)

\[
C_{\max} \ge C_{Bk}
\qquad \forall k\in K
\]

---

## Variable Domains

\[
x_{jk} \in \{0,1\}
\]

\[
C_{Ak},\, C_{Bk},\, C_{\max} \ge 0
\]

