 ### Sets
- \( J = \{1,\dots,12\} \) : set of jobs  
- \( M = \{A,B\} \) : set of machines  

Define:
- \( J_1 = \{1,\dots,7\} \) (order \(A \rightarrow B\))  
- \( J_2 = \{8,\dots,12\} \) (order \(B \rightarrow A\))  

---

### Parameters
Processing times:

\[
p_{Aj}, \quad p_{Bj} \quad \forall j \in J
\]

(Big‑M constant sufficiently large)

\[
M \ge \sum_{j \in J}(p_{Aj}+p_{Bj})
\]

---

### Decision Variables

\[
S_{mj} \ge 0 \quad \text{start time of job } j \text{ on machine } m
\]

\[
C_{\max} \ge 0 \quad \text{makespan}
\]

\[
x_{ijm} \in \{0,1\} \quad \forall i<j,\; m\in M
\]

\[
x_{ijm} =
\begin{cases}
1 & \text{if job } i \text{ precedes job } j \text{ on machine } m \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]

---

### Objective Function

\[
\min C_{\max}
\]

---

### Constraints

#### 1. Technological Order Constraints

For \( j \in J_1 \) (A → B):

\[
S_{Bj} \ge S_{Aj} + p_{Aj}
\]

For \( j \in J_2 \) (B → A):

\[
S_{Aj} \ge S_{Bj} + p_{Bj}
\]

---

#### 2. Machine Capacity Constraints (No Overlap)

For all \( i<j,\; m \in M \):

\[
S_{mi} + p_{mi} \le S_{mj} + M(1 - x_{ijm})
\]

\[
S_{mj} + p_{mj} \le S_{mi} + M x_{ijm}
\]

---

#### 3. Makespan Definition

\[
C_{\max} \ge S_{Aj} + p_{Aj} \quad \forall j \in J
\]

\[
C_{\max} \ge S_{Bj} + p_{Bj} \quad \forall j \in J
\]

---

#### 4. Variable Domains

\[
S_{mj} \ge 0
\]

\[
x_{ijm} \in \{0,1\}
\]

\[
C_{\max} \ge 0
\]

