\[
d_1=100,\; d_2=140,\; d_3=200,\; d_4=160
\]

Warehouse capacity:

\[
S=20
\]

Storage cost (thousand yuan / thousand m³):

If purchased in quarter \(i\) and sold in quarter \(j\),

\[
h_{ij} =
\begin{cases}
0, & j=i \\
70 + 100(j-i), & j>i
\end{cases}
\]

---

## **Decision Variables**

\[
x_{ij} \ge 0
\]

Amount purchased in quarter \(i\) and sold in quarter \(j\)  
(unit: thousand m³)

---

# **Objective Function**

\[
\max Z =
\sum_{i=1}^{4} \sum_{j=i}^{4}
\left( p_j - c_i - h_{ij} \right) x_{ij}
\]

(Maximize annual profit in thousand yuan)

---

# **Constraints**

---

## 1️⃣ Sales Limits (Demand Constraints)

For each quarter \(j\):

\[
\sum_{i=1}^{j} x_{ij} \le d_j
\qquad j=1,2,3,4
\]

---

## 2️⃣ Warehouse Capacity Constraints

Inventory at the **end of quarter \(k\)** equals all timber purchased up to \(k\) but sold after \(k\).

For each quarter \(k=1,2,3\):

\[
\sum_{i=1}^{k} \sum_{j=k+1}^{4} x_{ij} \le S
\]

Explicitly:

End of Winter:

\[
x_{12}+x_{13}+x_{14} \le 20
\]

End of Spring:

\[
x_{13}+x_{14}+x_{23}+x_{24} \le 20
\]

End of Summer:

\[
x_{14}+x_{24}+x_{34} \le 20
\]

(No constraint needed after Autumn since all must be sold.)

---

## 3️⃣ Nonnegativity

\[
x_{ij} \ge 0
\qquad \forall i \le j
\]

