# ✅ Final Optimized Mathematical Model

---

## Sets

\[
I=\{1,2,3\} \quad \text{(origins)}
\]
\[
J=\{A,B,C,D,E\} \quad \text{(destinations)}
\]

---

## Parameters

Supply:
\[
s_1=50,\quad s_2=100,\quad s_3=150
\]

Demand:
\[
d_A=25,\; d_B=115,\; d_C=60,\; d_D=30,\; d_E=70
\]

Unit transportation cost \(c_{ij}\):

\[
C=
\begin{bmatrix}
10 & 15 & 20 & 20 & 40 \\
20 & 10 & 15 & 30 & 30 \\
30 & 35 & 40 & 55 & 25
\end{bmatrix}
\]

---

## Decision Variables

\[
x_{ij} \ge 0 \qquad \forall i\in I,\; j\in J
\]

= amount transported from origin \(i\) to destination \(j\)

---

## Objective Function

\[
\min Z=\sum_{i\in I}\sum_{j\in J} c_{ij}x_{ij}
\]

---

## Constraints

### 1. Supply Constraints

\[
\sum_{j\in J} x_{ij}=s_i \qquad \forall i\in I
\]

### 2. Demand Constraints

\[
\sum_{i\in I} x_{ij}=d_j \qquad \forall j\in J
\]

### 3. Nonnegativity

\[
x_{ij}\ge 0 \qquad \forall i\in I,\; j\in J
\]

---

