- Total supply (90) exceeds total demand (70), and storage absorbs the surplus (20), so the model is balanced.

However, the model can be **slightly simplified** by eliminating the storage variables \( s_i \).  
Since

\[
s_i = \text{supply}_i - \sum_j x_{ij},
\]

we can substitute directly into the objective function and remove \( s_i \) and their constraints.

