# ✅ Final Optimized Mathematical Model

### Decision Variables

\[
x_{ij} \ge 0
\quad
(i=1,2,3;\; j=A,B,C)
\]

= units shipped from origin \( i \) to destination \( j \).

---

### Objective Function

Minimize total transportation and storage cost:

\[
\min Z =
\sum_{i=1}^{3} \sum_{j \in \{A,B,C\}} c_{ij} x_{ij}
+5(20-\sum_{j}x_{1j})
+4(40-\sum_{j}x_{2j})
+3(30-\sum_{j}x_{3j})
\]

Substituting and simplifying (dropping constants):

\[
\min Z =
\sum_{i=1}^{3} \sum_{j} (c_{ij}-h_i) x_{ij}
\]

where storage costs are:

\[
h_1=5,\quad h_2=4,\quad h_3=3
\]

Thus the adjusted costs become:

\[
\begin{aligned}
\min Z =
&(-4)x_{1A}+(-3)x_{1B}+(-3)x_{1C} \\
&+(-3)x_{2A}+0x_{2B}+1x_{2C} \\
&+(-1)x_{3A}+0x_{3B}+0x_{3C}
\end{aligned}
\]

(Equivalent to original objective up to an additive constant 350, which does not affect optimality.)

