\[
\begin{aligned}
&10,15,20,20,40\\
&20,40,15,30,30\\
&30,35,40,55,25
\end{aligned}
\]

Shortage penalty cost (large number):

\[
M \gg \max(c_{ij})
\]

---

## Final Linear Programming Model

### Objective Function

\[
\min Z =
\sum_{i=1}^{3} \sum_{j=1}^{5} c_{ij} x_{ij}
+ M \sum_{j=1}^{5} s_j
\]

Explicitly:

\[
\begin{aligned}
\min Z = 
&10x_{11}+15x_{12}+20x_{13}+20x_{14}+40x_{15} \\
&+20x_{21}+40x_{22}+15x_{23}+30x_{24}+30x_{25} \\
&+30x_{31}+35x_{32}+40x_{33}+55x_{34}+25x_{35} \\
&+ M(s_1+s_2+s_3+s_4+s_5)
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### Constraints

### 1️⃣ Warehouse Capacity

\[
\sum_{j=1}^{5} x_{ij} \le S_i \quad (i=1,2,3)
\]

\[
\begin{aligned}
x_{11}+x_{12}+x_{13}+x_{14}+x_{15} &\le 50 \\
x_{21}+x_{22}+x_{23}+x_{24}+x_{25} &\le 100 \\
x_{31}+x_{32}+x_{33}+x_{34}+x_{35} &\le 150
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 2️⃣ Demand Balance (Corrected)

\[
\sum_{i=1}^{3} x_{ij} + s_j = D_j
\quad (j=1,\dots,5)
\]

\[
\begin{aligned}
x_{11}+x_{21}+x_{31}+s_1 &= 25 \\
x_{12}+x_{22}+x_{32}+s_2 &= 105 \\
x_{13}+x_{23}+x_{33}+s_3 &= 60 \\
x_{14}+x_{24}+x_{34}+s_4 &= 30 \\
x_{15}+x_{25}+x_{35}+s_5 &= 70
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 3️⃣ Factory Production Capacity

\[
\sum_{i=1}^{3} \sum_{j=1}^{5} x_{ij} \le 270
\]

---

### 4️⃣ Non‑negativity

\[
x_{ij} \ge 0, \quad s_j \ge 0
\]

