# ✅ Optimized and Standardized Final Model

This problem is a **minimum-cost flow (transshipment) problem**.

---

## Sets

\[
N = \{X,Y,A,B,C\}
\]

Supply nodes:
\[
S = \{X,Y\}
\]

Demand nodes:
\[
D = \{A,B,C\}
\]

---

## Parameters

Supply:
\[
b_X = 70,\quad b_Y = 55
\]

Demand:
\[
b_A = -35,\quad b_B = -40,\quad b_C = -50
\]

(Check: total supply = total demand = 125 ✅)

Distance (cost) matrix \(c_{ij}\):

Supply–Supply:
\[
c_{XY}=12,\quad c_{YX}=10
\]

Supply–Demand:
\[
\begin{aligned}
&c_{XA}=10,\quad c_{XB}=14,\quad c_{XC}=12 \\
&c_{YA}=15,\quad c_{YB}=12,\quad c_{YC}=18
\end{aligned}
\]

Demand–Demand:
\[
\begin{aligned}
&c_{AB}=14,\quad c_{AC}=11 \\
&c_{BA}=10,\quad c_{BC}=4 \\
&c_{CA}=8,\quad c_{CB}=12
\end{aligned}
\]

---

## Decision Variables

\[
x_{ij} \ge 0 \quad \forall (i,j) \text{ where distance is defined}
\]

---

## Objective Function

\[
\begin{aligned}
\min Z =
&12x_{XY}+10x_{YX} \\
&+10x_{XA}+14x_{XB}+12x_{XC} \\
&+15x_{YA}+12x_{YB}+18x_{YC} \\
&+14x_{AB}+11x_{AC} \\
&+10x_{BA}+4x_{BC} \\
&+8x_{CA}+12x_{CB}
\end{aligned}
\]

