# ✅ Final Mathematical Model

### Sets
- \( S = \{1,2,3,4\} \) (strokes: Backstroke, Breaststroke, Butterfly, Freestyle)
- \( A = \{1,2,3,4,5\} \) (athletes: Zhao, Qian, Zhang, Wang, Zhou)

---

### Parameters

Let \( c_{ij} \) denote the time (seconds) for athlete \( j \) in stroke \( i \).

\[
C =
\begin{bmatrix}
37.7 & 32.9 & 33.8 & 37.0 & 35.4 \\
43.4 & 33.1 & 42.2 & 34.7 & 41.8 \\
33.3 & 28.5 & 38.9 & 30.4 & 33.6 \\
29.2 & 26.4 & 29.6 & 28.5 & 31.1
\end{bmatrix}
\]

---

### Decision Variables

\[
x_{ij} =
\begin{cases}
1, & \text{if athlete } j \text{ is assigned to stroke } i \\
0, & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]

---

### Objective Function

\[
\min Z = \sum_{i=1}^{4} \sum_{j=1}^{5} c_{ij} x_{ij}
\]

---

### Constraints

**(1) Each stroke is assigned exactly one athlete**

\[
\sum_{j=1}^{5} x_{ij} = 1, \quad \forall i = 1,2,3,4
\]

**(2) Each athlete is assigned to at most one stroke**

\[
\sum_{i=1}^{4} x_{ij} \le 1, \quad \forall j = 1,2,3,4,5
\]

**(3) Binary constraints**

\[
x_{ij} \in \{0,1\}, \quad \forall i,j
\]

---

This is the final optimized linear (binary integer) programming model suitable for Gurobi implementation.
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Sets
strokes = ["Backstroke", "Breaststroke", "Butterfly", "Freestyle"]
athletes = ["Zhao", "Qian", "Zhang", "Wang", "Zhou"]

# Parameters: time matrix c[i][j]
c = {
    ("Backstroke", "Zhao"): 37.7,
    ("Backstroke", "Qian"): 32.9,
    ("Backstroke", "Zhang"): 33.8,
    ("Backstroke", "Wang"): 37.0,
    ("Backstroke", "Zhou"): 35.4,

    ("Breaststroke", "Zhao"): 43.4,
    ("Breaststroke", "Qian"): 33.1,
    ("Breaststroke", "Zhang"): 42.2,
    ("Breaststroke", "Wang"): 34.7,
    ("Breaststroke", "Zhou"): 41.8,

    ("Butterfly", "Zhao"): 33.3,
    ("Butterfly", "Qian"): 28.5,
    ("Butterfly", "Zhang"): 38.9,
    ("Butterfly", "Wang"): 30.4,
    ("Butterfly", "Zhou"): 33.6,

    ("Freestyle", "Zhao"): 29.2,
    ("Freestyle", "Qian"): 26.4,
    ("Freestyle", "Zhang"): 29.6,
    ("Freestyle", "Wang"): 28.5,
    ("Freestyle", "Zhou"): 31.1,
}

# Create model
model = gp.Model("200m_Medley_Relay_Assignment")

# Decision variables
x = model.addVars(strokes, athletes, vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="x")

# Objective function
model.setObjective(
    gp.quicksum(c[i, j] * x[i, j] for i in strokes for j in athletes),
    GRB.MINIMIZE
)

# Constraints: Each stroke assigned exactly one athlete
for i in strokes:
    model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(x[i, j] for j in athletes) == 1, name=f"Stroke_{i}")

# Constraints: Each athlete assigned to at most one stroke
for j in athletes:
    model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(x[i, j] for i in strokes) <= 1, name=f"Athlete_{j}")

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal total time: {model.objVal:.2f} seconds\n")
    print("Relay team assignment:")
    for i in strokes:
        for j in athletes:
            if x[i, j].x > 0.5:
                print(f"{i}: {j} ({c[i, j]} seconds)")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
```
