\]

Total number of assignments:
\[
\sum_{i\in P}\sum_{j\in T} x_{ij} = 5
\]

Each person takes at least one and at most two tasks:
\[
1 \le \sum_{j\in T} x_{ij} \le 2 \quad \forall i \in P
\]

Binary:
\[
x_{ij} \in \{0,1\}
\]

---

# (b) Either X or Z takes two tasks; Y and R take one (all five tasks assigned)

### Objective
\[
\min Z = \sum_{i\in P}\sum_{j\in T} c_{ij} x_{ij}
\]

### Constraints

Each task assigned exactly once:
\[
\sum_{i\in P} x_{ij} = 1 \quad \forall j \in T
\]

Y and R take exactly one task:
\[
\sum_{j\in T} x_{Yj} = 1
\]
\[
\sum_{j\in T} x_{Rj} = 1
\]

X and Z together take remaining three tasks:
\[
\sum_{j\in T} x_{Xj} + \sum_{j\in T} x_{Zj} = 3
\]

Limit for X and Z:
\[
1 \le \sum_{j\in T} x_{Xj} \le 2
\]
\[
1 \le \sum_{j\in T} x_{Zj} \le 2
\]

Binary:
\[
x_{ij} \in \{0,1\}
\]

---

# (c) Each person completes one task; A and B must be completed; one of C, D, F left unassigned

### Objective
\[
\min Z = \sum_{i\in P}\sum_{j\in T} c_{ij} x_{ij}
\]

### Constraints

Each person assigned exactly one task:
\[
\sum_{j\in T} x_{ij} = 1 \quad \forall i \in P
\]

Tasks A and B must be assigned:
\[
\sum_{i\in P} x_{iA} = 1
\]
\[
\sum_{i\in P} x_{iB} = 1
\]

Among C, D, F exactly two are assigned:
\[
\sum_{i\in P} (x_{iC} + x_{iD} + x_{iF}) = 2
\]

Each task assigned at most once:
\[
\sum_{i\in P} x_{ij} \le 1 \quad \forall j \in T
\]

Binary:
