5.19 A certain product can be processed on any one of four machines: A, B, C, or D. The setup cost, unit production cost, and maximum production capacity for each machine are shown in Table 5-7.The factory needs to produce 2,000 units of the product.Question: How should production be allocated among the machines to minimize the total cost? Formulate the mathematical model.  

