【数学模型】:
 **Decision variables (for \(k=1,2,3,4\))**

\[
\begin{aligned}
x_k &:= \text{units purchased in month } k \\
y_k &:= \text{units sold in month } k \\
S_k &:= \text{inventory at the beginning of month } k \\
E_k &:= \text{inventory at the end of month } k
\end{aligned}
\]

(All variables are nonnegative integers.)

---

## Objective Function

Maximize total profit:

\[
\max Z = 12y_1 + 9y_2 + 13y_3 + 17y_4
- (10x_1 + 9x_2 + 11x_3 + 15x_4)
\]

---

## Constraints

### 1. Initial Inventory

\[
S_1 = 500
\]

---

### 2. Sales Limited by Available Inventory

\[
y_k \le S_k \qquad k=1,2,3,4
\]

---

### 3. End-of-Month Inventory Balance

\[
E_k = S_k - y_k \qquad k=1,2,3,4
\]

---

### 4. Inventory Transition (Purchases Available Next Month)

\[
S_{k+1} = E_k + x_k \qquad k=1,2,3
\]

(Note: \(x_4\) does not affect the 4-month horizon inventory.)

---

### 5. Warehouse Capacity Constraint

\[
S_k \le 1000 \qquad k=1,2,3,4
\]

\[
E_k \le 1000 \qquad k=1,2,3,4
\]

(Equivalently, ensuring \(S_{k+1} = E_k + x_k \le 1000\) for \(k=1,2,3\).)

---

### 6. Nonnegativity and Integrality

\[
x_k,\, y_k,\, S_k,\, E_k \ge 0 \quad \text{and integers}
\]

