# Final Mathematical Model

### Sets
\[
G = \{A,B,C,D,E\}
\]
\[
K = \{1,2,3,4,5\}
\]

### Parameters
\[
p_A = 0.10,\quad
p_B = 0.25,\quad
p_C = 0.30,\quad
p_D = 0.20,\quad
p_E = 0.15
\]

### Decision Variables
\[
x_{gk} =
\begin{cases}
1 & \text{if grade } g \text{ is sorted in position } k \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]

### Objective Function
Minimize expected sorting workload:

\[
\min Z = \sum_{g \in G} \sum_{k \in K} p_g \, k \, x_{gk}
\]

### Constraints

1. Each grade assigned exactly one position:
\[
\sum_{k \in K} x_{gk} = 1
\qquad \forall g \in G
\]

2. Each position assigned exactly one grade:
\[
\sum_{g \in G} x_{gk} = 1
\qquad \forall k \in K
\]

3. Binary variables:
\[
x_{gk} \in \{0,1\}
\qquad \forall g \in G,\; k \in K
\]

---

### Optimal Sorting Order (from model logic)

Since minimizing \( \sum p_g k \) implies assigning smaller \(k\) to larger \(p_g\),

Optimal order:

\[
C \rightarrow B \rightarrow D \rightarrow E \rightarrow A
\]

(Descending order of proportions.)

